Class Square

  • java.lang.Object
    • WHG.Block
      • WHG.Square
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Renderable, Updateable

    public class Square
extends Block
implements Renderable, Updateable
    This class is used to draw and update the red square in the game.

      • onCollision

        public void onCollision(Block block)
        This method checks to see if the square is colliding with anything. If it was with a wall, it sets the position of the square back to being inside the wall; if it was with a ball, it sets the hit instance variable to true so that the square cannot move; if it was with a coin, the coin disappears.
        Specified by:
        onCollision in class Block
        Parameters:
        block - is the block it is checking the collision against the square with.

      • reset

        public void reset()
        This resets the square back to its original position, sets hit to false so that the square can move again, and sets the death count to increment by one.
